# Overview

This packages allows to obtain Trusted Timestamps from
[OriginStamp](https://originstamp.org) for hashes. The hashes can be
from anything, files, R objects, numbers, text, … whatever you can
calculate a hash from.

It is only available on github, so you can install it by using devtools:

``` r
if (!require(devtools)) {
  install.packages("devtools")
  library(devtools)
}
```

Before yo can use the package, you have to get an API key from
[OriginStamp]().

Due to the limimtations of sha1, it is recommended to use sha256, by
using e.g.

``` r
library(openssl)
fnc <- file.path( dir, fn )
f <- file( fnc, open = "rb" )
hash <- as.character( openssl::sha256( f ) )
close(f)
rm(f)
```
